  "prompt": "What is the best time of day to drink a single coffee to keep you going for the longest duration?",
  "response": "The best time of day to drink a single coffee to maximize its effects and keep you energized for the longest duration depends on your natural circadian rhythm and cortisol levels. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the optimal timing:\n\n1. **Wait 1\u20132 Hours After Waking Up**: Cortisol, a hormone that promotes alertness, naturally peaks in the morning. Drinking coffee during this peak can reduce its effectiveness. Instead, wait 1\u20132 hours after waking (e.g., 9:00\u201310:00 AM for most people) to drink your coffee, when cortisol levels start to decline.\n\n2. **Avoid Late Afternoon or Evening**: Caffeine has a half-life of about 5\u20136 hours, meaning it can stay in your system for a long time. Drinking coffee too late in the day (e.g., after 2:00\u20133:00 PM) can interfere with your sleep, reducing its overall benefit.\n\n3. **Pair Coffee with Sustained Energy**: To maximize the duration of its effects, pair your coffee with a balanced meal or snack containing protein, fiber, and healthy fats. This can slow caffeine absorption and prevent a crash.\n\nBy drinking your coffee mid-morning and supporting it with proper nutrition, you can extend its energizing effects throughout the day while avoiding sleep disruptions.",
